<item>
            <title>[IO-179] StringIndexOutOfBounds exception on FilenameUtils.getPathNoEndSeparator</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/IO-179</link>
                <project id="12310477" key="IO">Commons IO</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;public void testFilenameUtils() &lt;/p&gt;
{
 String path = &quot;/foo.xml&quot;;
 org.apache.commons.io.FilenameUtils.getPathNoEndSeparator(path);
 }


&lt;p&gt;Leads to:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;java.lang.StringIndexOutOfBoundsException: String index out of range: -1&lt;br/&gt;
	at java.lang.String.substring(String.java:1768)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.apache.commons.io.FilenameUtils.doGetPath(FilenameUtils.java:705)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.apache.commons.io.FilenameUtils.getPathNoEndSeparator(FilenameUtils.java:683)&lt;/p&gt;


</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Javadoc says that method is text based. In any case, the problem has been reproduced in Windows and Linux.&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
